emocracy_and_Electoral_Assistance|International IDEA]] |dead-url=no |quote=Mongolia is sometimes described as a semi-presidential system because, while the prime minister and cabinet are collectively responsible to the SGKh, the president is popularly elected, and his/her powers are much broader than the conventional powers of heads of state in parliamentary systems. |author-link1=<!-- Munkhsaikhan Odonkhuu --> |website=ConstitutionNet |access-date=2016-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160225144740/http://www.constitutionnet.org/news/mongolia-vain-constitutional-attempt-consolidate-parliamentary-democracy |archive-date=2016-02-25}}</ref>
